HEADWORD: Gazeebo
<hw>Ga*zee"bo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Humorously formed
from <ets>gaze</ets>.]</ety> <def>A summerhouse so situated as to
command an extensive prospect.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

